snippet.textDisplay: His speech was best and then MJ. I read a quote somewhere and it goes “a wife that looses a husband is a widow a husband that looses a wife is a widower, a child that looses a parent is an orphan, but there is no word for a parent that looses a child, because the pain is unimaginable.” So when Shaq mentioned his parents it made my heart smile, before he was anything he was a son. It saddens me to see his own wife not mention the parents. Also she lost a child and when she spoke of her, her emotions were more raw then when she spoke of her husband, so she should understand that they also lost a child and a grandchild. Anyways speech was amazing, I wish this memorial honored all of the deaths. Rest In Peace to all of the people and I pray for the ones left behind who have to live with this sadness.

REGRET MY ABSENCE MY LOVE ... BUT LET ME GO
When I reach the end of the trip
And the sun has set for me
I don't want a dark and funeral ritual
Why mourn a liberated soul?

REGRET MY ABSENCE A LITTLE MY LOVE... BUT NOT TOO LONG
And don't let the pain overwhelm you
Remember the special LOVE we shared

REGRET MY ABSENCE MY LOVE ... BUT LET ME GO
'Cause it's a trip that we all have to do
And that everyone must accomplish alone
It is part of the path that God has shown us
And leads us into his blessed household
When you suffer from loneliness and melancholy
Turn to those who are our friends, families, our kids
And forget your grief by doing good

REGRET MY ABSENCE MY LOVE... BUT PLEASE LET ME GO..

snippet.textDisplay: Lakers, I feel the deepest grief for vanessa and the kids. But before Kobe became a basketball player, husband, father and award winner etc, he was a son and a brother. You all except shaq who had the kindness to mention his parents , make his passing so much painful. He had issues with his parents as most of us all do at one point in our lives but if he knew he had less time or if he lived long, he would have made up with them , don’t you think? Continuing the malice by omitting that he was a son and a brother in your tributes makes we all look bad and a disrespect to God and nature. He died the most painful death because his daughter died with him. I feel deep rooted pain to imagine what he and the other parents went through just before they died knowing their children who have not started life are going to die with them. Now in his memorial , you omit the parents in your tributes who God used to give him life ? Because they had issue? Oh may his and that of Gigi and the others souls Rest In Peace. Lesson to learn for me, make peace quickly with anyone not just your parents, no matter the hurt, for tomorrow is not promised to anyone. ,goodbye dear Kobe and Gigi. Goodbye. The world has lost a lot in your deaths and in the deaths of the other people especially the children. No parents should bury their kids. Today Kobe’s parents and Vanessa are burying their kids. But worst are parents dying with their kids. Oh Kobe and the other parents on board the craft, I am really really sorry. 😭😭😭😭. May God almighty have mercy on them all, receive their souls in heaven and comfort the living as we try to be better and do better as we await our own time to die. Amen.
